  "prompt": "Where is the RAW filter in Photoshop CS6?",
  "response": "In Photoshop CS6, the RAW filter is actually called Camera Raw, and you access it in a few different ways:\n\n1. When opening a RAW file:\n- If you double-click a RAW file, Camera Raw will automatically open\n\n2. After opening a RAW file:\n- Filter > Camera Raw Filter\n\n3. For existing images:\n- Go to Filter > Camera Raw Filter\n- Or use the keyboard shortcut Shift + Ctrl + A (Windows) or Shift + Command + A (Mac)\n\nNote: If the Camera Raw Filter option is grayed out, the layer might need to be converted to a smart object first. To do this, right-click the layer and select \"Convert to Smart Object\" before accessing the Camera Raw Filter.",
